The Telegraph - Calcutta
		 Friday, April 02, 2004  Merchant suspended 
 BY OUR TURF CORRESPONDENT				 										Calcutta: Jockey Amyn Merchant was suspended by the RCTC stewards for unsatisfactory riding of his charge Mythical Star in the first race of Thursday afternoon the Desert Night Handicap. Stewards, after a long inquiry handed Merchant a split sentence.				 										The first part of jockeys sentence begins from April 11 and concludes on April 30. The part two of penalty starts from July 1 and ends of August 31. He is, however, permitted to ride races between months of May and June.
